<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-05-05T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-05-05T09:00:00-05:00" n="549" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">365D.1163/73: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-05T15:00:00+01:00">May 5, 1937—3
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 5—11:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>200. Embassy’s 159, April 14, 7 p.m. Foreign Office informs me that
                                Ministry of Colonies has ascertained that the report of the
                                expulsion of the three members of the American Bible Missionary
                                Society, referred to in paragraph 2 of the Embassy’s telegram 152 of
                                April 9, 6 p.m., is unfounded and that the missionaries in question
                                are still in Addis Ababa.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>